## Problem
On narrow mobile viewports, terminal output lines wrap aggressively due to `overflow-wrap: anywhere` and `word-break: break-word` on `.terminal-line`. Each single log line becomes 3-4 visual lines of fragmented text, making it nearly unreadable.

## Changes
**File:** `frontend/src/styles.css`

Extend the existing `@media (max-width: 720px)` block (currently at line ~9606) with terminal-specific rules:

```css
@media (max-width: 720px) {
  /* ... existing saved-command-dialog rules ... */

  /* Terminal: allow horizontal scroll instead of aggressive line wrapping */
  .terminal-output {
    overflow-x: auto;
    -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;
    padding: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .terminal-line {
    white-space: pre;
    overflow-wrap: normal;
    word-break: normal;
  }
}
```

### Rationale
- `white-space: pre` preserves the line as-is without wrapping
- `overflow-x: auto` on `.terminal-output` lets users horizontally scroll long lines
- `-webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch` ensures smooth scrolling on iOS/Android
- Reduced padding (`var(--space-sm)` = 4px vs current 6px) gives a few more pixels of usable width

