## Context

When `comfyui_generate` (or any image-producing tool) runs during a chat turn, the generated image data flows to the LLM context via `toolResultMessages` but is **never** added to the `ChatMessage.Images` field that the frontend renders. The assistant message has no images attached, so nothing shows up in chat.

## Changes — `internal/services/chat.go`

### 1. Add optional attachment fields to `ChatStreamEvent`

```go
type ChatStreamEvent struct {
    // ... existing fields ...
    ImageAttachment *ChatImageAttachment `json:"imageAttachment,omitempty"`
    VideoAttachment *ChatVideoAttachment `json:"videoAttachment,omitempty"`
}
```

### 2. Add `attachChatImage` helper method

```go
func (s *SystemService) attachChatImage(workspaceID string, streamID string, messageID string, attachment ChatImageAttachment) {
    s.mutateChatMessage(workspaceID, messageID, func(message *ChatMessage) {
        message.Images = append(message.Images, attachment)
    }, ChatStreamEvent{
        WorkspaceID:     workspaceID,
        StreamID:        streamID,
        MessageID:       messageID,
        Type:            "image_attached",
        ImageAttachment: &attachment,
    })
}
```

Same pattern for `attachChatVideo` using `Videos` slice and `VideoAttachment`.

### 3. Hook into `executeToolCall` (after `updateToolActivity`, ~line 850)

After a successful tool result, check if the result contains image/video data and attach it:

```go
// Attach images from tool results to the chat message for display.
if imgMsg, ok := toolResultImageMessage(call.Function.Name, result); ok {
    for _, part := range imgMsg.ContentParts {
        if part.ImageURL != nil && part.ImageURL.URL != "" {
            s.attachChatImage(workspace.ID, streamID, messageID,
                ChatImageAttachment{
                    Source:  "tool",
                    Name:    call.Function.Name + "-generated",
                    DataURL: part.ImageURL.URL,
                })
        }
    }
}

// Same for videos via toolResultVideoMessage(...)
```

